Fix build issues and enhance CI/CD workflow for SpotApp
- Removed outdated build success summary documentation. - Updated Android build.gradle.kts to enable R8 optimizations and improve signing configuration. - Adjusted iOS Podfile to set deployment target to 12.0 for compatibility. - Deleted obsolete build-all-platforms.sh script and streamlined build process. - Improved build.sh script to handle project root navigation and clean previous builds. - Removed redundant fix-all-build-issues.sh script and integrated fixes into dedicated scripts. - Simplified fix-android-build.sh to focus on R8 issues and keystore validation. - Enhanced fix-ios-build.sh to improve dependency management and error handling. - Updated build output messages for clarity and added troubleshooting steps.

Enhance iOS and Android build scripts for SpotApp
- Updated `fix-ios-build.sh` to improve iOS build process, including cleaning, dependency management, and code generation. - Added comprehensive build summary and troubleshooting steps for iOS builds. - Created `BUILD_ISSUES_FIX_SUMMARY.md` to document identified issues and fixes related to keystore, Gradle, and iOS deployment targets. - Developed `BUILD_SUCCESS_SUMMARY.md` to summarize successful build fixes and results. - Enhanced `build-all-platforms.sh` to support both Android and iOS builds with improved error handling and logging. - Introduced `fix-all-build-issues.sh` for comprehensive fixes across Android and iOS, including keystore regeneration and dependency management. - Updated `Podfile` to set iOS deployment target to 13.0 for Firebase compatibility. - Improved CI/CD considerations and added emergency fallback strategies for builds.

fix: Update Firebase and Google Sign-In dependencies; enhance iOS build scripts
- Updated Firebase dependencies in pubspec.yaml to latest compatible versions. - Migrated Google Sign-In from version 6.x to 7.0.0, addressing breaking API changes. - Enhanced iOS build script to clean and install dependencies more robustly. - Created a comprehensive Podfile to resolve GoogleUtilities version conflicts. - Added automated scripts for fixing iOS build issues and preparing builds. - Documented migration and dependency resolution processes in markdown files.
Enhance multi-platform CI/CD pipeline: Add iOS build support, implement fallback strategies for Android builds, and improve error handling in build scripts
Enhance SpotApp v4.0: Implement multi-platform support with iOS build pipeline, update README and release notes, and improve settings page versioning
